An Act relative to institutions of higher education.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 148 of Chapter 149 of the General Laws is hereby amended by
2 inserting after the words “engaged in agricultural work” when they first appear, the phrase "and
3 employees of nonprofit institutions of higher education."
4 SECTION 2. Section 148 of Chapter 149 of the General Laws is hereby amended by
5 inserting the following sentence: "With respect to any claim or cause of action seeking any legal
6 or equitable remedy or relief commenced on or after July 1, 2024, a nonprofit institution of
7 higher education shall be immune from civil liability under claims alleging that the institution’s
8 payment of wages on a monthly basis violated this Section."
